news.title: Blackstone sells 5.7 crore units in Embassy Office Parks REIT for over Rs 2,000 crore
news.para: Embassy Office Parks REIT is the country's first real estate investment trust (REIT), sponsored by realty firm Embassy group and Blackstone.

news.title: Dues mount, Noida authority to cancel allotment of two plots to Logix group
news.para: The group was to develop a retail unit – mall and multiplex – and office space in Sector 105 and had similar plans for Sector 124 with a limited number of residential suites.

news.title: Cops in Mumbai to investigate Unitech promoters' jail activities
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate had earlier submitted a report in the Supreme Court elaborating on how the promoters — Ajay and Sanjay Chandra — had allegedly threatened witnesses, apart from operating a free communications network and sending instructions from inside the jail.

news.title: Fitch warns an Evergrande default may have broad China economic effects
news.para: Evergrande is scrambling to raise funds to pay its many lenders and suppliers, as it teeters between a messy meltdown with far-reaching impacts, a managed collapse or the less likely prospect of a bailout by Beijing.

news.title: China Evergrande's liquidity crisis deepens, report flags interest payment miss
news.para: Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development (MOHURD) held a meeting with the banks this week, the Bloomberg report said on Wednesday, citing sources familiar with the matter. It added that Evergrande is still discussing with banks the possibility of extending payments and rolling over some loans.

news.title: China: Evergrande Group's debt struggle rattles investors
news.para: ​Evergrande Group appears likely to be unable to repay all of the 572 billion yuan (USD89 billion) it owes banks and other bondholders, financial rating agencies say.

news.title: Goldman Sachs, JPMorgan warn of Evergrande's debt woes spillover risks
news.para: The developer, which has liabilities of nearly two trillion yuan ($305 billion), is trying to raise funds to pay lenders and suppliers as it teeters between a managed collapse and the more distant prospect of a bailout by Beijing.

news.title: China's cooling measures curb new home price growth, property investment
news.para: Average new home prices grew at their slowest pace since December on a monthly basis, and since January on an annual basis, as authorities stepped up property curbs this year, from capping banks' lending to the sector to restricting purchases.

news.title: China's Wanda raises nearly $6 billion for commercial property management unit: Sources
news.para: Hong Kong-based private equity firm PAG led the fundraising, with $2.8 billion for the unit, Wanda Light Asset Commercial Management Co, said three of the sources.

news.title: NGT forms panel to submit report on plea against construction in Mohali
news.para: ​A bench headed by NGT Chairperson Justice Adarsh Kumar Goel constituted a five-member joint Committee comprising officials from the Environment Ministry, Central Pollution Control Board, SEIAA Punjab, Punjab State Pollution Control Board and District Magistrate, Mohali.

news.title: DDA to set up board of enquiry to consider objections, suggestions on Delhi master plan
news.para: The LG, among other decisions, directed constitution of a board of enquiry, for hearing and considering objections and suggestions offered by the public on the draft Master Plan of Delhi 2041, officials said.

news.title: Dharma Productions inks office lease renewal pact with Karan Johar, group company
news.para: The company has leased the space from the company’s director Karan Johar and one of the affiliated companies Yashwan Productions, who are the owners of this property.

news.title: Pune civic body organises Lok Adalat to resolve pending property tax cases
news.para: "As many as 500 cases will be resolved using this alternative dispute resolution mechanism. The civic body will offer 50% discount on penalty if the tax defaulter agrees to clear the dues," said Hemant Rasane, chairman of the standing committee.

news.title: ED arrests Patliputra Builders' MD in Patna in money laundering case
news.para: ​​Anil Kumar Singh, MD of Patliputra Builders Limited, was taken into custody on September 7 and a special Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) court sent him to five-day ED custody on Tuesday.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh HC pulls up officials for going soft on illegal sand mining
news.para: ​When the court sought a reply from the mining department, the assistant government pleader for mining said temporary permission was given for mining on the island lands.
